    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focal point in **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 82.13. Facing a favorable matchup against Roki Sasaki (xERA 5.52), **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from a strong dynamic platoon advantage (+14%) and favorable wind conditions. While he is relegated to the #8 spot, his elite sprint speed remains our primary weapon in a category where we prioritize volume. Joining him as a high-upside play is **Junior Caminero** (73.53), whose raw power against Bailey Ober is bolstered by a strong SP skill matchup (+12%). **Trea Turner** (68.86) and **Kyle Schwarber** (65.76) also project as foundational pieces today, with both benefiting from strong top-of-the-order positioning and favorable matchups against Bryce Elder.\n\nThe decision to bench **Victor Scott II** (39.50) was the most difficult call of the morning; his score fell just narrowly below our 40.0 floor, primarily due to a tough draw against Bryan Woo (xERA 3.30) and an unfavorable #9 spot in the order. Despite our obsession with speed, we could not justify the start given the pitcher's elite profile. Elsewhere, we are keeping a close eye on **Hyeseong Kim** (57.68) and **Josh Smith** (44.87); **Hyeseong Kim** receives a slight boost from wind conditions, but **Josh Smith** remains a volatility risk against Jeffrey Springs, where his platoon disadvantage is only marginally offset by the SP's slow delivery. We are continuing to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar** on the IL, while **Zac Veen** remains stashed in the minors. With lineups still pending for **Gary Sanchez**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Colt Keith**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Kyle Schwarber**, **Josh Smith**, **Yordan Alvarez**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, and **Junior Caminero**, we remain prepared to adjust should official batting orders significantly crater these projections.",
